objects.name: T1566: Phishing
objects.description: Adversaries may send phishing messages to gain access to victim systems. All forms of phishing are electronically delivered social engineering targeted at a user individual, company, or industry.

objects.name: T1589: Gather Victim Identity Information
objects.description: Adversaries may gather information about victim identity that can be used during targeting. Information about identities may also reveal more about the victim and their role within an organization.

objects.name: T1059: Command and Scripting Interpreter
objects.description: An adversary may use command and scripting interpreters to execute commands, scripts, or binaries. These interfaces and languages provide ways of interacting with computer systems and are a common feature across many different platforms.

objects.name: T1059.001: PowerShell
objects.description: Adversaries may use PowerShell to perform a number of actions, including discovery of information and execution of code. PowerShell is a powerful interactive command-line interface and scripting environment included in the Windows operating system.

objects.name: T1543: Create or Modify System Process
objects.description: Adversaries may create or modify system-level processes to repeatedly execute malicious payloads as part of persistence. Modifications to system processes may mask malicious activity from security tools and monitoring.
